      "markdown": "# SUPPORT General Reinfercemont: allotted to INFANTRY (SUPPORT)\n\nORIGINAL\nDUPLICATE\nTRIPLICATE\n\nCopy designation to be shown\nby striking out terms not applicable.\nRCAmc.\n\nPB\ncupational\n\nry Form Completed.\n\nM.F.M. 2\n(Combining M.F.M. 103)\n750M-6-43 (9375)\nH.Q. 1772-39-1645\n\nCorps\nM-97407\n\nCANADIAN ARMY\nENROLMENT AND ATTESTATION PAPER\nRichard\n\nFINGERPRINTED AND PHOTOGRAPHEL\n\nWSG.\n\nCOMPLETED\n\n2\\. Present Address\nGen Del Chambery Sask\n\n3\\. (a) Date of birth\n5 Sept 1904\n\n(unknown)\n(unknown)\n\n(b) Place of birth\n(Country)\nNORWAY\n(County or Province)\n(unknown)\n(Town or Township)\n(unknovm)\n\n4\\. (a) Place of birth of Father\nNorway\n\n(b)\n**\nMother\n(Country)\nNorway.\n(unknown)\n(unknown)\n\n5\\. Nationality\nCanadian (Parents Naturalized 1914, Manle Creek, Sask.)\n(To what country do you now owe allegianee) if naturalized give cortif. no. date and place of issue. If not naturalized so state.\n\n6\\. Religion (state denomination)\nLutheran\n\n7\\. Trade or calling (a) Farm Laborer\n\n(a) Name and address of last employer :\nMr Roy QUENNEL\nGen Del Chanbery Sask\n\n(b) How long employed\n6 yrs\n\n9\\. Married, Widower or Single\nSingle\nIf married, how many children\nNa\n\n10\\. Name of Next-of-Kin Mrs Malena AADLAND\n\n11\\. Relationship\n\n12\\. Address of Next-of-Kin Gen Del ChamberyeSask\n\n13\\. Previous Service (Navy, Army or Air Force) Units and dates\nNone\n\n14\\. (a) Former war service\nNone\n\n(b) In the armed forces of what country\nNa\n\n(c) Dates of such Service\nNa\n\n15\\. Decorations and medals, if any\nNone\n\n16\\. I do solemnly declare that the above particulars are true\nRichard Rilli\nSignature of Recruit, or in the case of N.R.M.A. personnel who\nrefuse to sign, signature of officer under Regn. 8 (d) (I)\nR.A.S.R. 1941\n\n16\u03b1 CERTIFICATE OF MAGISTRATE, JUSTICE OF THE PEACE ATTESTING OR ENROLLING OFFICER\n\nThe above-named was cautioned by me that if he made any false answers to any of the above\nquestions he would be liable to be punished as provided by law.\nThe above questions and answers were then read to the above named in my presence.\nI have taken care that he understands each question, and that his answer to each question has\nbeen duly entered as replied to,\nat\nReginaSask\nthis\n3rd\nday of\nSep t\n19\n43\nMackeo\nCapte\nFor 0pp. #12 Dist Dap ot\nRECINA Sade\n\nOffice or Rank and Unit\nor appointment.\n\n17, 18 AND 19 WILL NOT BE COMPLETED UNLESS A MAN ENLISTS FOR GENERAL SERVICE ANYWHERE.\nDECLARATION TO BE MADE BY MAN ON ATTESTATION\n\nIRichard AADLAND\nhereby engage to serve in any Active Formation or\nUnit of the Canadian Army so long as an emergency, i.e., war, invasion, riot or insurrection, real or\napprehended, exists, and for the period of demobilization after said emergency ceases to exist, and in\nany event for a period of not less than one year, provided His Majesty should so require my services.\n\nDate\nSeptember 3rd 1943\n(Signature of Recruit)\nRichard achand\n\n18\\.\nOATH TO BE TAKEN BY MAN ON ATTESTATION\n\nI. Richard AADLAND\ndo sincerely promise and swear (or solemnly declare)\nthat I will be faithful and bear true allegiance to His Majesty.\n\nWitness\n(Name)\nocusico\nCap1\n(Hank)\n\n(Signature of Recruit)\nRichard Oradland\n\n19\\. The above named recruit has made and signed the declaration and taken the oath before me.\n\nat Regina, Sask:\nthis\n3ml\nday of September\n19 43\nMauico\nbar\n(Signature of Magistrate, Justice or Attesting Officer.)\n\n12th Dist, Depot, CA(A') Regina (Office or Rank and Unit or appointment)\n\nN.B.-ATTENTION IS DRAWN TO THE FACT THAT ANY PERSON WILFULLY MAKING A FALSE ANSWER TO ANY OF THE\nABOVE QUESTIONS IS LIABLE TO A PENALTY OF SIX MONTHS' IMPRISONMENT.\n\n(Christian Names)\n\n1\\.\nAADLAND\n(Surname)\nTae 88k0\n\nRegimental Number\n2.106876\n\nSignature of Magistrate, Justice Attesting or\nEnrolling Officer.\n\n17\n\n(County or Province)\n(Town or Township)\nMother\n",
